    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Ensuring Diverse Leadership Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Federal Reserve Act to require that in making the appointment of a president, a Federal Reserve Bank must interview at least one individual reflective of gender diversity and one reflective of racial or ethnic diversity.</p> <p>The bill amends numerous banking-, finance-, and trade-related Acts to make references to officials (including those to the Chairman of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System) gender-neutral. </p>]]></text>
